revision.text:
'''{{class|Actor}}'''

{{c|bool '''LookForEnemies'''(bool ''allaround'', LookExParams ''params'' }}={{c| null)}}

== Usage ==
This actor function makes the calling actor look for its enemies. Functions similarly to '''[[A_LookEx]]''', but uses a '''{{struct|LookExParams}}''' struct to determine its behavior instead of arguments.

{{: LookFor parameters}}

== Examples ==
An example of how this function can be called:
<syntaxhighlight lang="csharp">
LookExParams params;
params.fov = 180;
params.flags = LOF_NOSOUNDCHECK;
params.minDist = 0;
params.maxDist = 1024;
params.maxHearDist = 2048;
LookForEnemies(false, params);
</syntaxhighlight>

